# Development Workflow Guide

## Environment Setup
1. Node.js version is specified in [.node-version](mdc:.node-version) and [.nvmrc](mdc:.nvmrc)
2. Package manager is pnpm (see [pnpm-lock.yaml](mdc:pnpm-lock.yaml))
3. Development environment is managed by mise (see [mise.toml](mdc:mise.toml))

## Key Development Tasks

### Adding New Pages
1. Create new `.astro` files in [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages)
2. Use layouts from [src/layouts/](mdc:src/layouts)
3. Add components from [src/components/](mdc:src/components)

### Adding New Components
1. Create components in [src/components/](mdc:src/components)
2. Use TypeScript for type safety
3. Follow the project's component structure

### Content Management
1. Add content in [src/content/](mdc:src/content)
2. Configure content collections in [src/content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts)

### Styling
1. Use UnoCSS for styling (see [uno.config.js](mdc:uno.config.js))
2. Global styles are in [src/styles/](mdc:src/styles)

### Internationalization
1. Configure languages in [src/i18n.ts](mdc:src/i18n.ts)
2. Add translations in the appropriate language files

## Code Quality
1. Follow ESLint rules (see [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs))
2. Use TypeScript for type safety
3. Follow the project's coding standards
